\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. F. elegans} Boiss., {\i Elenchus }92 (1838). Stems (40-)60-90 cm × 1·5-2·2 mm, scabrid above. Leaves 0·4-0·5 mm wide, strongly scabrid, acute, the lowest as long as the uppermost; veins 5, the sclerenchyma forming a ring; rib 1, rarely with 2 indistinct lateral ribs; sheaths open, very scabrid, stramineous or violet-tinged; ligule (2-)2·5-4 mm, acute. Panicle 8-14 cm, slightly interrupted, the branches densely hispid. Spikelets (6·5-)7-8 mm, greenish or slightly variegated with violet. Upper glume 3-3·9 × 1·3-1·7 mm, ovate-lanceolate, broadly scarious. Lemma 3·9-4·8 × 2·2-2·3 mm, ovate, with a wide scarious margin, unawned. Anthers slightly more than ½ as long as palea. Ovary glabrous or sparsely hairy. 2n = 28.{\i  Mountain woods and scrub; calcifuge. Spain, N. Portugal}. Hs Lu.
\par

