\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. F. burnatti} St-Yves,{\i  Annu. Cons. Jard. Bot. Genève}{\b  15/16}: 347 (1913). Stems 15-25 cm × 1·2 mm, scabrid above. Leaves 0·5-0·7(-0·9) mm wide, smooth, slightly pungent; veins 5-7; ribs 3-5, prominent, the lateral with sclerenchyma above, the main sclerenchyma forming a ring; sheaths of non-flowering shoots more or less transversely corrugated; ligule 5-7 mm, silvery-scarious. Panicle 4-7 cm, lax, the branches patent at anthesis, scabrid, filiform. Spikelets 9-10 mm, shining, yellowish-green variegated with violet. Upper glume 5-5·5 × 2-2·5 mm, ovate-lanceolate, broadly scarious. Lemma 5·5-6 × 2-2·7 mm, lanceolate, narrowly scarious above, with an awn 2-3 mm. Palea subglabrous on the surface, densely ciliolate on 2/3 of the keels. Anthers much more than ½ as long as palea. 2n = 14.{\i  Limestone rocks. • Mountains of N. Spain.} Hs.
\par

