\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. F. valida} (Uechtr.) Pénzes,{\i  Borbásia }{\b 3}: 13 (1941) ({\i F. varia }subsp. {\i valida} Uechtr.). Stems 65-106 cm × 1·3-4 mm. Lowest leaf (1/28)1/25-1/6 as long as the uppermost; veins (7-)9-11, the sclerenchyma forming a ring; ribs 7-9, prominent, all with a sclerenchyma strand above; ligule (0·7-)1-1·8(-2·5) mm, truncate. Panicle 9-13 cm, lax, nodding, much interrupted, the branches slender, shortly hairy. Spikelets greenish, slightly variegated with violet. Upper glume 6-7 × 2·3-2·6 mm, ovate-lanceolate, broadly scarious, usually obtuse. Lemma 7·1-9·1 × 2·8-3·2 mm, oblong-lanceolate, long-acuminate, broadly scarious above; awn 1-1·8 mm.{\i  Siliceous rocks and open pinewoods,} 1500-2600 {\i m. • W. Bulgaria and N. Greece.} Bu Gr.
