\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 25. F. scabriculmis} (Hackel) K.Richter, {\i Pl. Eur.}{\b  1}: 104 (1890). Stems (25-)33-55 cm. Leaves (0·3-)0·4-0·6(-0·8) mm wide, subpungent; rib 1 (rarely with 1-2 low, lateral ribs); sclerenchyma usually in a ring; sheaths closed for less than 4 of their length; ligule 0·8-1·7 mm, ciliolate. Panicle lax, erect to slightly nodding, the branches scabrid. Spikelets (9-) 10·3-14·5 mm, green, variegated with violet. Upper glume long-acuminate, with a narrow scarious margin. Lemma long-acuminate, with an awn up to 1·7 mm. Palea as long as the lemma, scabrid on the surface above, long-ciliate on the keels. Anthers c. ½ as long as palea. •{\i  S. Alps.} Ga He It.
