\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. F. quadriflora} Honckeny, {\i Vollst. Syst. Verz.} 268 (1782) ({\i F. pumila} Vill.). Stems (6-)10-20(-30) cm, scabrid below the panicle. Leaves (0·5-)0·6(-0·8) mm wide, scabrid above, scarcely pungent, the lowest 1/6-1/4 as long as the uppermost; veins 5(-7); ribs 1, sometimes with low lateral ribs; sclerenchyma usually in separate strands; sheaths slightly scabrid; ligule 0·5-1 mm, truncate. Panicle 2-4 cm, lax, erect, with few spikelets, the branches scabrid. Spikelets (7-)8-9(-10) mm, usually glaucous, variegated with intense violet. Upper glume 3·8-5·2 × 1·5-2 mm, ovate-lanceolate, long-acuminate. Lemma 4-6 × 2·27 mm, broadly lanceolate, acuminate, with a scarious margin above; awn 0·2-1·3 mm. Palea strongly scabrid on the surface, long-ciliate on the keels. Anthers at least ½ as long as palea. 2n = 14.
